comments.body:
Thanks @edsantiago @TomSweeneyRedHat for the review, I'll make those corrections shortly.

@baude or anyone else recall a http -> https change on the RTD side while I was on "Vacation"?   That's definitely what broke, (we didn't allow https previously).  Knowing that it was not caused by a sun-spot or other high-energy particle would help me feel better in sticking with a manual CORS-metadata maintenance scheme.

Otherwise, I can automate this, despite my security-hairs standing on end.  I'm just not sure it will do much overall, beyond requiring even more documentation and adding more complexity :confused:
